<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Claim2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Claim,</orth> vb., to challenge, to demand as a right: <bibl n="shak. luc 1715" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1715</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.135" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. V, 4, 135</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.2.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 2, 82</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.1.110" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 110</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.139" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 139</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.231" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 231</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.3.168" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 3, 168</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.4.43" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 3.2.75" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 1.91" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.94" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.1.44" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 1, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.256" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 256</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.167" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 4, 167</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.239" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 239</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.239" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 239</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.2.35" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.2.35" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 35</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.1" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.7.46" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 7, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.50" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 1, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.2.91" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.469" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 469</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.1.15" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 1, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.5.39" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.5.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 5, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.194" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 3, 194</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.2.83" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 83</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.3.126" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 3, 126</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.401" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 2, 401</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.2.130" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 2, 130</bibl>. <emph>To c. a promise</emph> == to remind a person of a promise: <cit><quote>I c. the promise for her heavenly picture,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.92" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. IV, 4, 92</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I'll c. that promise at your highness' hands,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.197" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 1, 197</bibl></cit>. With <emph>from</emph>: <cit><quote>virtue --s from beauty beauty's red,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 59" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 59</bibl></cit>. With <emph>of</emph>: <cit><quote>--s marriage of me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 4.4.159" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 4, 159</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jn 1.122" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 122</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.153.159" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 153</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.194" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 1, 194</bibl>.<lb />Absolutely: <cit><quote>to bar your highness --ing from the female,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.92" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 92</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.92" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 92</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.2.19" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 2, 19</bibl>.
